cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT

The paper introduces a new approach to design reservoir topologies for Echo State Networks, which are commonly used in machine learning for time series prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the experimental assessment of the proposed approach, which involves measuring predictive accuracy and memory capacity, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of bidirectional jump connections, which are commonly used in control systems, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
